v0.017

          - Don't pass the compiler's optimization flags to the ld command. On
            systems where these two commands are different (AIX and some
            version of HPUX among them), the ld command may not accept these
            optimization flags. (Dave Rolsky, GH #9)

Don't pass compiler's optimize flags to ld

On systems where the ld command is not the same as the compiler, there's no
reason to assume that these flags are valid for the linker. I encountered this
on AIX and HPUX IA64, but this could apply anywhere, AFAICT.

v0.016

          - Stable release without modifications since 0.015
Updated Changes

v0.015

          - Fix eucb test to check result object [#113686]
          - Use $Config{ld} on unix too
Use $Config{ld} on unix too

Fix eucb test to check result object [#113686]

CBuilder's have_compiler doesn't properly check if the linking result
is actually a loadable object, creating false positives on
dysfunctional compilers.

This is more of a workaround than a real fix, a better solution would be
not to use cbuilder at all anymore. This is a work in progress.

v0.014

          - Create temporary directory under local directory
          - Use better temp template names
Use better temp template names

Create temporary directory under local directory

If /tmp is mounted noexec, it could otherwise trigger a false negative
when trying to load the resulting loadable object.
